{
    "id": "welcome/run-tests",
    "title": "Run the Test Suite",
    "description": "Learn how to run DSPACE's automated tests to ensure your changes are correct.",
    "image": "/assets/quests/run_tests_terminal_dashboard.jpg",
    "npc": "/assets/npc/dChat.jpg",
    "start": "start",
    "dialogue": [
        {
            "id": "start",
            "text": "Tests catch regressions and keep reviews fast. Learn the core commands, then ace the quiz.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "primer",
                    "text": "Show me the commands."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "primer",
            "text": "Quick sanity check: npm run qa:smoke (type-check, link-check, item validation, test:ci, no Playwright). Full pre-PR suite: npm run test:pr (includes grouped Playwright). No browsers? SKIP_E2E=1 npm test.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "quiz-1",
                    "text": "Quiz me."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "quiz-1",
            "text": "Which command is the fastest sanity check that mirrors CI without Playwright?",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "quiz-2",
                    "text": "npm run qa:smoke"
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "retry-sanity",
                    "text": "npm run test:pr"
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "retry-sanity",
                    "text": "npm run lint"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "retry-sanity",
            "text": "qa:smoke is the quick CI-parity run without Playwright E2E.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "quiz-1",
                    "text": "Try again"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "quiz-2",
            "text": "Which command runs the full pre-PR suite with grouped Playwright tests?",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "quiz-3",
                    "text": "npm run test:pr"
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "retry-pr",
                    "text": "npm run qa:smoke"
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "retry-pr",
                    "text": "npm run build"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "retry-pr",
            "text": "test:pr is the full pre-PR suite, including grouped Playwright E2E.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "quiz-2",
                    "text": "Back to it"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "quiz-3",
            "text": "If Playwright browsers are missing, how do you skip E2E tests?",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "prep-repo",
                    "text": "SKIP_E2E=1 npm test"
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "retry-e2e",
                    "text": "E2E_SKIP=1 npm test"
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "retry-e2e",
                    "text": "npm test --no-e2e"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "retry-e2e",
            "text": "Use SKIP_E2E=1 npm test when browsers are unavailable.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "quiz-3",
                    "text": "Got it"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "prep-repo",
            "text": "Start by creating a GitHub repo for your fork so you can mirror CI locally.",
            "options": [
